  'lab.final_formula_desc': 'The net force equals the rate of change of momentum',
  'lab.derivation_subtitle': 'Newton ke doosre qanoon se formula tak mantiqi taraqqi ki pairwi karein',
  'lab.mass_label': 'Mass (m)',
  'lab.initial_velocity_label': 'Initial Velocity (vi)',
  'lab.final_velocity_label': 'Final Velocity (vf)',
  'lab.time_interval_label': 'Time Interval (Δt)',
  'lab.force_placeholder': 'Force in Newtons...',
  'lab.incorrect_feedback': 'Ghalat hai. Yad rakhein raftaar simt badalti hai!',
  'lab.footer_prefix': 'Numberon ka hisab chahiye?',
  'lab.footer_suffix': 'header mein hai',
  'lab.step1_label': "Newton's Second Law",
  'lab.step2_label': 'Acceleration = Rate of Velocity Change',
  'lab.step3_label': 'Substitute a into F = ma',
  'lab.step4_label': 'Recognize Momentum p = mv',
  'lab.step1_detail': "🚴 Aap 10 m/s se muhallay ki gali mein cycle chala rahe hain jab ek bacha ball ke peeche bhagta hua nikalta hai. Aap brakes lagate hain. Newton's 2nd law kehta hai F = ma — brake pads rim ko dabaate hain, ek force lagate hain jo aap ko decelerate karti hai.",
  'lab.step2_detail': 'Aap ki speed 2 seconds mein 10 m/s se 0 ho jati hai. Tabdeeli ki sharah acceleration hai: a = (0 − 10)/2 = −5 m/s². Aap ka body aage ko jhukta hai — yeh inertia hai jo change ke khilaf mazahemat kar rahi hai. Negative sign? Aap slow ho rahe hain, matlab force backward hai.',
  'lab.step3_detail': 'Aap + aap ki bike = 80 kg. F = 80 × (0 − 10)/2 = −400 N. Mass taqseem karein: F = (80×0 − 80×10)/2 = (0 − 800)/2. Aap ki brakes 400 N force laga rahi hain — ek chotay adult ke weight ke barabar!',
  'lab.step4_detail': 'Momentum p = mv aap ki "quantity of motion" ko zahir karta hai. Aap ne p = 80 × 10 = 800 kg·m/s se start kiya. 2 seconds mein, woh momentum zero ho jata hai. To F = Δp/Δt = (0 − 800)/2 = −400 N. Force sirf yeh hai ke momentum kitni tezi se change hota hai. Yahi wajah hai ke airbags jaan bachate hain — woh impact time Δt ko barhate hain, jis se force F kam ho jati hai!',
  'lab.trace_step1': 'Step 1: F = ma',
  'lab.trace_step2': 'Step 2: a = Δv/Δt',
  'lab.trace_step3': 'Step 3: F = m(Δv/Δt)',
  'lab.trace_step4': 'Step 4: F = Δp/Δt',
  'lab.real_life_airbags': 'Airbags crash ke doran impact ke time ko barhate hain — Δt ko 0.01s se 0.1s karne se force 10 guna kam ho jati hai, yahi wajah hai ke airbags peak force kam karke jaanen bachate hain.',
  'lab.practice_cricket_q': 'Ek cricket ball (0.16 kg) 30 m/s se phenki jaati hai aur 40 m/s se mukhalif simt mein wapas mari jaati hai. Contact time: 0.01 s.',
  'lab.practice_force_q': 'Bat ke zariye lagai gayi average force kya hai?',
  'lab.practice_hint': 'Δp = m(vf − vi) = 0.16 × (40 − (−30)) = 0.16 × 70 = 11.2 kg·m/s. F = Δp/Δt = 11.2 / 0.01 = ?',
  'lab.practice_correct_feedback': 'F = Δp/Δt istemal karte hue, 11.2 / 0.01 = 1120 N — ek person ke weight se bhi zyada!',

  // --- Recoil Derivation ---
  'lab.force_title': 'Derivation: Force aur Velocity Change',
  'lab.recoil_title': 'Derivation: Gun Recoil Velocity',
  'lab.recoil_subtitle': 'Momentum ke tahafuz se recoil formula hasil karne ka tareeqa',
  'lab.recoil_final_desc': 'Bandook bullet ki simt ke mukhalif simt mein pichay hati hai',
  'lab.recoil_step1_label': 'Conservation of Momentum',
  'lab.recoil_step2_label': 'Before Firing: Everything at Rest',
  'lab.recoil_step3_label': 'After Firing: Bullet + Gun Move',
  'lab.recoil_step4_label': 'Solve for Recoil Velocity',
  'lab.recoil_step1_detail': '🎯 Aap shooting range mein hain, 4 kg ki rifle aap ke kandhe par hai. Aap saans lete hain, nishana lagate hain, aur trigger dabaate hain. Gun + bullet ek "isolated system" banate hain — firing se pehle ka momentum firing ke baad ke momentum ke barabar hona chahiye.',
  'lab.recoil_step2_detail': 'Firing se pehle, rifle aur 10 g bullet dono aap ke haathon mein bilkul still hain. Kul initial momentum = 0. Sab kuch khamosh, mustaqil — zero motion, zero momentum. Phir firing pin strike karta hai.',
  'lab.recoil_step3_detail': 'BANG! Bullet 400 m/s se aage ki taraf rockets hai. Uska momentum: 0.01 × 400 = 4 kg·m/s aage. Tahafuz ke mutabiq, gun ka momentum −4 kg·m/s pichay aap ke kandhe mein hona chahiye: m_b·v_b + m_g·v_g = 0.',
  'lab.recoil_step4_detail': 'Hal karte hue: v_g = −(m_b·v_b)/m_g = −(0.01 × 400)/4 = −1 m/s. Negative sign? Gun aap ke kandhe mein 1 m/s se pichay latkti hai. Bhaari gun kam recoil karti hai — yahi wajah hai ke competition shooters bhaari rifles istemal karte hain. Rockets bhi yahi kaam karte hain: exhaust neeche jata hai, rocket upar jata hai!',
  'lab.recoil_trace1': 'pi = 0 (dono aaram par)',
  'lab.recoil_trace2': 'mb×vb = {mb} × {vb} = {mbvb}',
  'lab.recoil_trace3': 'mg×vg hona chahiye: {mgvg}',
  'lab.recoil_trace4': 'Recoil velocity: {recoil} m/s',
  'lab.recoil_real_life': 'Firefighters ko hose istemal karne se pehle apni jagah mazboot karni hoti hai — aage shooting water utni hi pichay ki force (recoil) paida karti hai, bilkul rocket ki tarah jo gas nikaal kar space mein chalta hai.',
  'lab.recoil_practice_q': 'Ek 4 kg rifle 12 g bullet 500 m/s se fire karti hai.',
  'lab.recoil_practice_q2': 'Rifle ki recoil velocity kya hai?',
  'lab.recoil_practice_hint': 'mb = 12g = 0.012 kg, vb = 500 m/s, mg = 4 kg. vg = −(mb×vb)/mg = −(0.012×500)/4',
  'lab.recoil_correct_feedback': 'Sahi! vg = 1.5 m/s. Rifle sirf 1.5 m/s pichay hati hai kyunki yeh bullet se kaafi bhaari hai.',
  'lab.recoil_incorrect_feedback': 'Ghalat hai. vg = (mb × vb) / mg = (0.012 × 500) / 4 istemal karein',
  'lab.recoil_bullet_mass_label': 'Bullet Mass',
  'lab.recoil_bullet_vel_label': 'Bullet Velocity',
  'lab.recoil_gun_mass_label': 'Gun Mass',
  'lab.recoil_placeholder': 'Velocity (m/s)...',
  'lab.recoil_adjust_desc': 'Sliders adjust karein, phir FIRE! daba kar conservation of momentum ko amal mein dekhein.',

  // --- Orbital Derivation ---
  'lab.orbital_title': 'Derivation: Satellite Orbital Speed',
  'lab.orbital_subtitle': 'Speed aur circular motion ki bunyadi tareefon se v = 2πr/T hasil karna',
  'lab.orbital_final_desc': 'Orbital speed = circumference ÷ orbital period',
  'lab.orbital_step1_label': 'Average Speed Formula',
  'lab.orbital_step2_label': 'Distance in One Orbit = Circumference',
  'lab.orbital_step3_label': 'Time = Orbital Period T',
  'lab.orbital_step4_label': 'Substitute to Get Orbital Speed',
  'lab.orbital_step1_detail': '🛰️ Tasawur karein aap 100 km oonchai wale pahad se ek baseball ufqi tor par pheink rahe hain. Woh neeche ghanoosdaar raasta banata hai aur door ja girta hai. Jaise jaise aap door phenkna chahte hain, aapko tez phenkna hoga. Average speed = distance / time — yeh simple idea orbital mechanics ka beej hai.',
  'lab.orbital_step2_detail': 'Ab tasawur karein ki aap 7.8 km/s se pheink rahe hain — itni tez ke Zameen us wicket ke neeche usi sharah se mudti hai jis sharah woh girti hai! Ball kabhi zameen nahi lagti — woh orbit karta hai. Ek mukammal orbit mein, woh circle ka circumference travel karta hai: d = 2πr, jahan r Earth ke center se distance hai.',
  'lab.orbital_step3_detail': '408 km Earth ke oopar (ISS altitude), ek mukammal orbit T = 92.7 minutes leti hai — yeh orbital period hai. ISS crew har roz 16 sunrise aur sunset dekhte hain kyunki woh itni tez orbit karte hain.',
  'lab.orbital_step4_detail': 'v = 2πr/T = 2π × 6,779,000 m / 5,562 s ≈ 7,660 m/s — 27,000 km/h se bhi zyada! Oonche orbits aahista hain: Moon 384,000 km par sirf 1 km/s se orbit karta hai. Jitna ooncha jayenge, utna hi aaram se aap ka safar hoga.',
  'lab.orbital_trace1': 'Step 1: v = d/t',
  'lab.orbital_trace2': 'Step 2: d = 2πr = 2π × {r} m',
  'lab.orbital_trace3': 'Step 3: T = {T} s',
  'lab.orbital_trace4': 'Step 4: v = 2πr/T = {v} m/s',
  'lab.orbital_real_life': 'Geostationary satellites 35,786 km par har 24 hours mein ek baar orbit karte hain, Earth ki rotation se mila kar — is liye satellite TV dishes kabhi hilne ki zaroorat nahi hoti. Sirf 3 satellites poore globe ko cover kar sakte hain.',
  'lab.orbital_practice_q': 'ISS 408 km altitude par orbit karta hai. Earth radius = 6,371 km. T = 92.7 minutes.',
  'lab.orbital_practice_q2': 'Orbital speed ka hisab lagayein.',
  'lab.orbital_practice_hint': 'r = 408 + 6371 = 6779 km = 6,779,000 m. T = 92.7×60 = 5562 s. v = 2πr/T',
  'lab.orbital_correct_feedback': 'Sahi! ~7,658 m/s. ISS 7.66 km/s se travel karta hai — 27,000 km/h se bhi zyada, Earth ka 16 baar roz!',
  'lab.orbital_incorrect_feedback': 'Ghalat hai. r = 6,779,000 m, T = 5,562 s. v = 2π(6,779,000)/5,562. km ko m mein badlein!',
  'lab.orbital_radius_label': 'Orbit Radius',
  'lab.orbital_placeholder': 'Orbital speed (m/s)...',
  'lab.orbital_adjust_desc': 'Slider ko hilakar dekhein ke orbit radius speed aur period ko kaise affect karta hai.',

  // --- Liquid Pressure Derivation ---
  'lab.lp_title': 'Derivation: Liquid Pressure (P = ρgh)',
  'lab.lp_subtitle': 'Kaise P = ρgh pressure aur weight ki tareef se nikalta hai',
  'lab.lp_final_desc': 'Pressure = density × gravity × depth',
  'lab.lp_step1_label': 'Pressure = Force per Area',
  'lab.lp_step2_label': 'Force = Weight of Liquid Column',
  'lab.lp_step3_label': 'Volume = Area × Height',
  'lab.lp_step4_label': 'Cancel Area to Get P = ρgh',
  'lab.lp_step1_detail': '🏊 Aap ek boat se samandar mein kood kar neeche gote lagate hain. Aap ke kaano mein ek bechain karne wala pressure banta hai. Pressure = force / area — aap ke oopar paani ka column hai jiska weight hai, aur woh weight aap ke jism ke har square millimeter par dabaav dalta hai.',
  'lab.lp_step2_detail': 'Force pani ka weight hai: F = mg. Lekin m = ρV (density × volume). Seawater density 1,025 kg/m³ hai — yeh fresh water se bhaari hai, is liye samandar mein tairna asaan hota hai! F = ρ × V × g.',
  'lab.lp_step3_detail': 'Aap ke oopar pani ka volume = aap ke jism ka area × depth: V = A × h. To F = ρ × A × h × g. Dekhein area A zahir hota hai — ek chaura shakhs ke oopar zyada pani ka weight hota hai. Lekin aage kuch magical hota hai...',
  'lab.lp_step4_detail': 'P = F/A = (ρ × A × h × g)/A = ρgh. Area CANCEL ho jata hai! Kisi bhi gahrai par pressure sab ke liye ek jaisa hai chahe jism ki shakal kuch bhi ho. Sirf 10 m gahre mein, pressure double hokar 2 atmospheres ho jata hai. Free divers saalon training karte hain yeh pressure sahne ke liye — pressure aap ke lungs aur sinuses jaisi hawa ki jagahon ko crush kar deta hai.',
  'lab.lp_trace1': 'P = F/A = (ρ × V × g) / A',
  'lab.lp_trace2': 'V = A × h, to P = (ρ × A × h × g) / A',
  'lab.lp_trace3': 'A cancel: P = ρgh',
  'lab.lp_real_life': 'Submarines mote hull ke saath banayi jaati hain kyunki 300 m gahrai mein pani ka pressure 30 atmospheres hota hai — ordinary steel ko crush karne ke liye kafi hai. Jitna neeche jayenge, utna zyada pressure.',
  'lab.lp_practice_q': 'Ek submarine seawater (ρ = 1025 kg/m³) mein 30 m tak gota lagati hai.',
  'lab.lp_practice_q2': 'Us gahrai par pressure kya hai? (g = 9.81 m/s²)',
  'lab.lp_practice_hint': 'P = ρgh = 1025 × 9.81 × 30 = ?',
  'lab.lp_correct_feedback': 'Sahi! 301,658 Pa. Yeh ~3× atmospheric pressure hai! Submarines in forces ko sahne ke liye banayi jaati hain.',
  'lab.lp_incorrect_feedback': 'Ghalat hai. P = ρgh = 1025 × 9.81 × 30. Teenon ko multiply karein!',
  'lab.lp_depth_label': 'Depth (h)',
  'lab.lp_density_label': 'Density (ρ)',
  'lab.lp_placeholder': 'Pressure (Pa)...',
  'lab.lp_adjust_desc': 'Depth aur density adjust karke dekhein ke P = ρgh real values ke saath kaise kaam karta hai.',

  // --- Hydraulic Lift Derivation ---
  "lab.hydraulic_title": 'Derivation: Hydraulic Lift (Pascal ka Usool)',
  'lab.hydraulic_subtitle': 'Kaise Pascal ka principle ek choti force ko bhaari load uthane deta hai',
  'lab.hydraulic_final_desc': 'Output force = area ratio × input force',
  'lab.hydraulic_step1_label': "Pascal's Principle",
  'lab.hydraulic_step2_label': 'Pressure on Small Piston',
  'lab.hydraulic_step3_label': 'Same Pressure on Large Piston',
  'lab.hydraulic_step4_label': 'Solve for Output Force',
  'lab.hydraulic_step1_detail': '🔧 Aap ek mechanic hain jiske paas 1500 kg ki car hai jo uthani hai. Aap hydraulic jack ko frame ke neeche rakh kar handle pump karte hain. Blaise Pascal ne daryaft kiya ke pressure ek closed container mein fluid par equally transmitted hota hai. Aap jo pressure handle par banate hain woh car tak bina kisi kami ke pahunchta hai.',
  'lab.hydraulic_step2_detail': 'Chote piston (area = 0.005 m²) ko sirf 240 N se daba kar aap P₁ = 240/0.005 = 48,000 Pa create karte hain — jaise pen ki nok apni hatheli par dabaye. Chota area matlab choti force se bada pressure.',
  'lab.hydraulic_step3_detail': 'Pascal ke principle se, 48,000 Pa jo aap ne pump handle par banaya woh hydraulic fluid ke zariye BINA KISI KAMI KE transmit hota hai. P₂ = P₁ = 48,000 Pa. Fluid aap ki force ko invisibly wahan pahunchata hai jahan zaroorat hai.',
  'lab.hydraulic_step4_detail': 'F₂/A₂ = F₁/A₁, to F₂ = (A₂/A₁) × F₁ = (0.25/0.005) × 240 = 12,000 N! Aap ki 240 N push poori car utha deti hai. Mechanical advantage = 50×. Yahi principle aap ki car rokta hai jab aap brake pedal dabate hain, bade excavators control karta hai, aur dentist chairs bhi chlata hai!',
  'lab.hydraulic_trace1': 'P₁ = F₁/A₁ = {p1} Pa',
  'lab.hydraulic_trace2': 'P₂ = P₁ (Pascal ka Principle)',
  'lab.hydraulic_trace3': 'F₂ = P₂ × A₂ = {f2} N',
  'lab.hydraulic_trace4': 'Mech. Advantage: {ma}×',
  'lab.hydraulic_real_life': 'Car brakes hydraulic multiplication use karte hain — brake pedal par choti force (5 cm² piston) brake pads par 20× zyada force (100 cm² piston) create karti hai, jisse aap ka paon 2-ton car rok sakta hai.',
  'lab.hydraulic_practice_q': 'Hydraulic lift: A₁ = 0.005 m², A₂ = 0.25 m². Car weight = 12,000 N.',
  'lab.hydraulic_practice_q2': 'Kya minimum input force chahiye?',
  'lab.hydraulic_practice_hint': 'F₁ = F₂ × A₁/A₂ = 12,000 × 0.005 / 0.25',
  'lab.hydraulic_correct_feedback': 'Sahi! F₁ = 240 N. 50:1 mechanical advantage ke saath, 240 N 12,000 N uthata hai — yeh hydraulics ki taqat hai!',
  'lab.hydraulic_incorrect_feedback': 'Ghalat hai. F₁ = F₂ × A₁/A₂ = 12,000 × 0.005 / 0.25',
  'lab.hydraulic_small_area_label': 'Small Piston Area (A₁)',
  'lab.hydraulic_large_area_label': 'Large Piston Area (A₂)',
  'lab.hydraulic_input_force_label': 'Input Force (F₁)',
  'lab.hydraulic_placeholder': 'Input force (N)...',
  'lab.hydraulic_adjust_desc': 'Piston areas aur input force adjust karke force multiplication dekhein.',

  // --- Kinetic Energy Derivation ---
  'lab.ke_title': 'Derivation: Kinetic Energy (Eₖ = ½mv²)',
  'lab.ke_subtitle': 'Kaise Eₖ = ½mv² work aur Newton ke doosre law se nikalta hai',
  'lab.ke_final_desc': 'Kinetic energy = half × mass × velocity squared',
  'lab.ke_step1_label': 'Work-Energy Theorem',
  'lab.ke_step2_label': 'Substitute F = ma',
  'lab.ke_step3_label': 'Use Motion Equations',
  'lab.ke_step4_label': 'The t Cancels!',
  'lab.ke_step1_detail': '🛹 Aap ek bade half-pipe ke oopar hain, dil zor se dharak raha hai. Aap neeche aate hain, aur gravity kaam karti hai. Gravity aap par jo work karti hai woh aap ki kinetic energy mein badal jata hai: E_k = Work = F × d. Jitna tez dhalaan, utna zyada work gravity karti hai.',
  'lab.ke_step2_detail': 'Gravity aap ko force F = mg se kheenchti hai. Distance d jo aap travel karte hain woh aap ki speed se related hai. Rest se start karte hue, ramp par aap ki average speed v_avg = v/2 hai. To d = v_avg × t = (v/2) × t. E_k = (ma)(d) = m × a × (v/2 × t).',
  'lab.ke_step3_detail': 'Ramp par aap ki acceleration a = v/t hai (aap kitni jaldi speed v tak time t mein pahunchte hain). Plug karein: E_k = m × (v/t) × (v/2 × t). t numerator AUR denominator mein zahir hota hai. Kuch khoobsurat hone wala hai...',
  'lab.ke_step4_detail': 'Time cancel ho jata hai! E_k = m × v × v/2 = ½mv². Speed double karna matlab energy QUADRUPLE karna. Yahi wajah hai ke 100 km/h par car crash 50 km/h ke crash se 4× zyada destructive hota hai, aur skateboard par double height se girna sirf double nahi lagta — chaar guna zyada lagta hai!',
  'lab.ke_trace1': 'Eₖ = ½ × {m} × {v}²',
  'lab.ke_trace2': 'Eₖ = 0.5 × {m} × {vsq}',
  'lab.ke_trace3': 'Eₖ = {ke} J',
  'lab.ke_real_life': 'Ek car 100 km/h par 50 km/h wali car se 4× zyada kinetic energy rakhti hai. Yahi wajah hai ke speed limits maujood hain — stopping distance speed ke square ke saath barhti hai, aur crash energy double speed par quadruple hoti hai.',
  'lab.ke_practice_q': 'Ek 1000 kg car 20 m/s (72 km/h) par travel karti hai.',
  'lab.ke_practice_q2': 'Us ki kinetic energy kya hai?',
  'lab.ke_practice_hint': 'Eₖ = ½ × 1000 × 20² = ?',
  'lab.ke_correct_feedback': 'Sahi! 200,000 J. 40 m/s (144 km/h) par yeh 800 kJ hoti — chaar guna zyada! Is liye speed itni khatarnak hai.',
  'lab.ke_incorrect_feedback': 'Ghalat hai. Pehle velocity square karein: 20² = 400. Phir E = 0.5 × 1000 × 400.',
  'lab.ke_mass_label': 'Mass (m)',
  'lab.ke_vel_label': 'Velocity (v)',
  'lab.ke_placeholder': 'Energy (J)...',
  'lab.ke_adjust_desc': 'Mass aur velocity adjust karke v² effect ko first-hand dekhein.',

  // --- Gravitational PE Derivation ---
  'lab.gpe_title': 'Derivation: Gravitational PE (Eₚ = mgh)',
  'lab.gpe_subtitle': 'Kaise Eₚ = mgh work ki tareef se nikalta hai',
  'lab.gpe_final_desc': 'Potential energy = mass × gravity × height',
  'lab.gpe_step1_label': 'Work Done Against Gravity',
  'lab.gpe_step2_label': 'Force = Weight of Object',
  'lab.gpe_step3_label': 'Distance = Height Lifted',
  'lab.gpe_step4_label': 'Gravitational PE Formula',
  'lab.gpe_step1_detail': '🎢 Aap roller coaster car mein baithe hain aur pehli bari pahadi ki taraf click karte hue ja rahe hain. Chain lift mechanism groans karti hai jab yeh aap ko ooncha kheenchti hai. Har meter jo aap oopar jaate hain, energy store hoti hai. E_p = Work = F × S — motor gravity ke khilaf kaam karta hai aap ko uthane mein.',
  'lab.gpe_step2_detail': '500 kg car (plus aap!) ko constant speed par uthane ke liye zaroori force uske weight ke barabar hai: F = mg. Do passengers ke saath, total mass ≈ 700 kg, to F = 700 × 9.81 = 6,867 N — ek choti car ke weight ke barabar.',
  'lab.gpe_step3_detail': 'Pehli pahadi 45 meters oonchi hai — yeh vertical height S = h hai. Motor ka work: W = 6,867 × 45 = 309,015 J. Har joule gravitational potential energy ke tor par store hota hai, release hone ka muntazir.',
  'lab.gpe_step4_detail': 'E_p = mgh = 700 × 9.81 × 45 = 309,015 J — itni energy jo 60W bulb 85 minutes tak jala sakti hai! Crest par aap ek split second rukte hain... phir aap plunge karte hain. Woh stored PE kinetic energy mein convert hoti hai jab aap neeche race karte hain, loops aur corkscrews ke zariye aap ko power deti hai. Jitni oonchi pehli pahadi, utni zyada energy poori ride ke liye!',
  'lab.gpe_trace1': 'Eₚ = Work = F × S',
  'lab.gpe_trace2': 'F = m × g = {f} N',
  'lab.gpe_trace3': 'S = h = {h} m',
  'lab.gpe_trace4': 'Eₚ = mgh = {e} J',
  'lab.gpe_real_life': 'Hydroelectric dams paani ko oonchai par store karte hain — har kilogram paani 100 m par 981 J gravitational PE rakhta hai, jo turbines se gir kar electricity mein convert hota hai.',
  'lab.gpe_practice_q': 'Ek 5 kg backpack shelf par floor se 1.5 m oopar hai.',
  'lab.gpe_practice_q2': 'Us ki gravitational potential energy kya hai? (g = 9.81)',
  'lab.gpe_practice_hint': 'Eₚ = mgh = 5 × 9.81 × 1.5 = ?',
  'lab.gpe_correct_feedback': 'Sahi! 73.6 J. 2 kg kitab usi oonchai par sirf 29.4 J rakhti hai — kam mass = kam stored energy!',
  'lab.gpe_incorrect_feedback': 'Ghalat hai. Eₚ = m × g × h = 5 × 9.81 × 1.5',
  'lab.gpe_mass_label': 'Mass (m)',
  'lab.gpe_height_label': 'Height (h)',
  'lab.gpe_placeholder': 'Energy (J)...',
  'lab.gpe_adjust_desc': 'Mass aur height adjust karke dekhein ke Eₚ = mgh kaise scale karta hai.',

